backend.title: Junior Python Developer
backend.description: Technologies we useExpectedPythonAWSAbout the projectOur client is embarking on a groundbreaking project to develop a platform that enables consistent, continuous, and highly automated marking of financial curves. This platform will empower traders to create and share curves regularly throughout the day for end-of-day processing. The goal is to ensure access to reliable and transparent market snapshots, enhance interdepartmental communication, and yield improved quantitative results, such as risk parameters for VaR.START DATE: January 2024If you’re passionate about financial technology, have a background in banking, and possess the technical skills to drive innovation, we invite you to join our team and be part of this exciting project. Apply now and contribute to shaping the future of financial curve marking!Your responsibilitiesCollaborate with a dynamic team of developers to implement and enhance the automated marking platform.Contribute to the creation of curves, ensuring consistency and accuracy in the financial data.Utilize C# or Python programming skills to develop and maintain software components.Leverage AWS Cloud experience to optimize the platform’s performance and scalability.Apply knowledge of financial analyst processes to meet the project’s specific requirements.Work closely with traders to understand their needs and provide technical solutions.Ensure the platform meets high standards of security, efficiency, and reliability.Collaborate with team members to troubleshoot issues and implement improvements.Our requirementsBackground in banking or finance to understand the nuances of financial markets.Proven experience working with AWS Cloud services.Familiarity with financial analyst processes and workflows.Strong communication skills in English.
